  "informal_statement": "For any element a and sets s, t of type Set alpha: a is in s union t if and only if a is in s or a is in t.",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Cited directly via Mathlib's Set.mem_union, which unfolds this as essentially the definition of set union membership.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem set_mem_union : ∀ {α : Type} (a : α) (s t : Set α), a ∈ s ∪ t ↔ a ∈ s ∨ a ∈ t",
